QUALIFICATION: as stated by Keen, 1969, [in Moore, ed.] Treatise on invertebrate paleontology, N2: 637; Solenocurtis [Swainson, 1840, A treatise on malacology: 366], Solenocurtus [Sowerby, 1842, A conchological manual, ed. 2: 262], Solenicurtus [W. Clark, 1851, Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 2, 8: 471, 473], and Solencurtus [Coppi, 1881, Paleontologia modenese: 112] are incorrect subsequent spellings. Cyrtosolen was suggested by Herrmannsen, 1848, Indicis generum malacozoorum primordia, 2: 468, to be a more proper spelling, but it was not used as valid and is not an available name. See also Solenocurtus P. Fischer. Agassiz, 1839, Mémoires de la Société des Sciences Naturelles de Neuchâtel, 2: 42, 43, designated Solen caribaeus as type species, but this was not an originally included species. Solecurtus Agassiz [non Blainville, 1824], 1839 is listed in Neave, 1940, Nomenclator Zoologicus, 4: 218, as a separate entry, but is merely a misapplication of Solecurtus Blainville. Senior objective synonym of Macha Oken, 1835
